      "title": "Introducción a fracciones",
      "html": "<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"es\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Introducción a fracciones</title>\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; padding: 1rem; }\n    h1, h2, h3 { margin: 0.2em 0; }\n    .badge { display:inline-block; font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 999px; background:#eef; margin-right: .4rem; }\n    .example, .task { border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.8rem; margin: 0.8rem 0; }\n    .example h4, .task h4 { margin-top: 0; }\n    .note { font-size: .9rem; color:#333; background:#fafafa; padding:.6rem .8rem; border-left: 3px solid #ddd; border-radius:6px; }\n    .step { margin:.3rem 0; }\n    code.k { background:#f7f7f7; padding:.15rem .35rem; border-radius:4px; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Fracciones equivalentes</h1>\n<div><span class=\"badge\">Eje</span> Resolver problemas con fracciones en contexto</div>\n<p>Dos fracciones son equivalentes si representan la misma parte del todo.</p>\n<div class=\"example\">\n  <h4>Ejemplo</h4>\n  <p>\\(\\tfrac{1}{2} = \\tfrac{2}{4}\\) porque ambas son “la mitad”.</p>\n</div>\n\n</body>\n</html>",
